Question:
Find the second largest number in a list.

Input:
List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(2, 8, 5, 3, 8);

Solutions:-

Java 8 Streams find second largest using stream().sorted().skip(1).findFirst(). For input [2, 8, 5, 3, 8], returns 5 (largest=8, second=5).

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream → sorted descending → skip(1) → findFirst() → Optional.

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.Comparator;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Optional;

public class SecondLargest {
    public static Optional<Integer> findSecondLargest(List<Integer> nums) {
        return nums.stream()
                   .sorted(Comparator.reverseOrder())  // descending
                   .skip(1)                            // skip largest
                   .findFirst();                       // get second
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(2, 8, 5, 3, 8);
        findSecondLargest(nums).ifPresent(System.out::println);  // 5
    }
}

#Thought Process
Reverse sort (Comparator.reverseOrder()) puts largest first. skip(1) discards max. findFirst() grabs second largest. Single pass after sort (O(n log n)). Optional handles edge cases safely.

#Edge Cases Analysis
<2 elements: Empty Optional
All duplicates: Empty Optional (all same after skip)
Exactly 2 unique: Returns smaller
Null list: NPE
Null elements: NPE in sort—filter first
Empty: Empty Optional
